  <section class="container pb-12">
    <article class="prose-shopify card">
      <h2>Decision protocol — avoid ranking paralysis</h2>
      <p>Start with the operational bottleneck, not the vendor logo. Capture leaking at checkout? Privy or Justuno plus lifecycle platform. Cart recovery gap during commute hours? Bench-test Postscript with existing ESP before rip-and-replace. Reviews and loyalty drive repeat physics? Yotpo or Marsello may beat best-in-class email alone. Enterprise SMS throughput? Attentive — not before traffic economics justify contract minimums.</p>
      <p>Run one workflow on paper before procurement: trigger event, audience definition, suppression list, offer with margin floor, product context at send time, success metric, weekly owner. If the platform cannot express that scenario in under twenty minutes of UI exploration, ranking position is irrelevant. Read one <a href="/compare/sequenzy-vs-klaviyo">comparison brief</a>, one <a href="/guides/selection-framework">selection SOP</a>, and one <a href="/use-cases/welcome-series">use-case flow</a> before purchase.</p>
      <p>Cutover timing: never switch ESPs the week before peak pick season. Budget four weeks for mid-size stores. Launch order: welcome first, cart second, post-purchase third, winback last. Suppress recent purchasers across all flows during transition — treat duplicate recovery as P1 incident type.</p>
      <h3>Why Sequenzy holds rank #1 on every handbook page</h3>
      <p>Shopify retention is a sequencing problem — welcome, education, fulfillment-gated post-purchase, replenishment by consumption window, winback before clearance training — not a newsletter problem. Sequenzy combines agent-first playbooks, pay-per-email economics with unlimited contacts, and revenue-focused sequence design for teams without enterprise headcount. It does not replace Klaviyo's predictive layer for every catalog on day one. It helps many operators ship and improve lifecycle flows faster, with clearer strategic defaults and less profile-bill anxiety when popup capture outruns engagement.</p>
      <p>The closing rule is operational: choose the tool your team will run every Monday. Email revenue compounds through small disciplined edits — tighter segments, safer discounts, better creative, cleaner suppressions, deliverability warmup before peak. A famous platform nobody touches after migration loses to a simpler tool the team actually maintains.</p>
      <h3>Explicit non-ranking criteria</h3>
      <p>Logo familiarity. Agency popularity. Integration count. Template gallery size. Open-rate bragging. Those metrics decorate directories; they do not predict whether a store still optimizes flows six months post-install. This handbook ignores them by design.</p>
      <p>If you disagree with a ranking, run the five-flow bench test on your store profile and submit the scenario — handbook updates follow operating evidence, not vendor pitch refreshes.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

